{
  "title": "About Rcngraph Plugin",
  "story": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "f3a8d291b4c56e17",
      "text": "The Rcngraph plugin opens the RCN Graph Diagramming Tool in a full popup window linked to the wiki lineup. The wiki page title is passed to the tool as the default diagram name and appears in the browser tab."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "2e7c9f04a3b8d651",
      "text": "Create an item using the factory. Click Open Graph Tool to open the tool. Use -> Item to save the diagram as an SVG preview back into the wiki item. Use -> Wiki to send the diagram to the lineup as a ghost page — node labels become clickable internal wiki links, following Ward Cunningham's Enrich Any SVG pattern."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "c1d2e3f4a5b60001",
      "text": "Diagram types — CLD (Causal Loop): map feedback loops and system dynamics. EIP (Enriched Influence Pattern): influence networks with stakeholders, flows, and interventions. OPM (Object-Process Methodology): system structure and process using Dov Dori's ISO 19450 standard, with OPL sentences and Cypher export. VSM (Viable System Model): recursive governance structure following Stafford Beer. NRM (Neighbourhood Risk Management): incident and risk analysis. Wardley: Wardley mapping on an evolution/visibility canvas. Triples: reifiable RDF-style triples with meta-edges for knowledge graph authoring."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "d2e3f4a5b6c70002",
      "text": "Import and export: MDL/Vensim CLD, Graphviz .dot, XMILE, Cypher, Wardley JSON, and CSV. Multi-trace edges, node and edge layers, canvas legend, and Print are available in all modes."
    },
    {
      "type": "rcngraph",
      "id": "8d4e2a7f1c9b3065",
      "text": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "4b6f8e3d9c2a1705",
      "text": "Developed by Marc Pierson with Claude Sonnet 4.6 (Anthropic) for the ReLocalize Creativity Network. Source: [[https://github.com/marpie1/wiki-plugin-rcngraph]]. Published on npm as wiki-plugin-rcngraph."
    }
  ],
